    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Corbin Carroll** (74.01) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92) leading our offensive charge. **Corbin Carroll** is an auto-start, benefiting from a favorable matchup against Sproat and a robust 0.372 xwOBA, while **Vinnie Pasquantino** is poised to exploit a high-value spot in the order against Severino, buoyed by significant park and platoon advantages. **Josh Naylor** (71.58) rounds out our top-tier plays, as his clean matchup against Bradley allows him to leverage his power profile effectively. We are also banking on **Brice Turang** (64.04) and **Kyle Karros** (63.06) to provide efficient production; **Kyle Karros** specifically benefits from an elite SP matchup against Williamson, making him a sneaky high-upside play despite his lower slot in the order.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench involved **Alex Freeland**, whose score of 49.99 kept him in consideration until the final projection run. Ultimately, the efficiency ceilings of **Dalton Rushing** and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, combined with the aggressive base-stealing potential we covet, pushed him out of the starting nine. While we remain cautious of the volatility surrounding **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Jose Caballero** against Eovaldi\u2019s 3.17 xERA, their positional scarcity and potential for game-changing stolen bases keep them in the mix. Investors should note the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Vinnie Pasquantino**; any shift away from the #3 spot would necessitate a re-evaluation of his dynamic platoon projections. We have opted to keep **Austin Riley** on the pine today, as he faces a brutal test against Skubal, a matchup that stifles his profile and renders him a sub-optimal start relative to our current depth.",
